<subsection><title>Check Your Understanding</title>
<p><ol>
<li><p>In Activity 1, describe the differences between the graphs of <m>y=x^2</m> and <m>y=x^3</m>.</p></li>     
<li><p>What connection do you see between the graphs of <m>y=x^2</m> and <m>y=\sqrt{x}</m>, and between the graphs of <m>y=x^3</m> and <m>y=\sqrt[3]{x}</m> ?</p></li>
<li><p>Explain how we use asymptotes to help us sketch a graph.</p></li>
<li><p>Which of the functions in this Lesson are undefined at <m>x=0</m> ?</p></li>
</ol></p></subsection>

<subsection><title>Wrap-Up</title>
<p>In this Lesson, we worked on the following skills and goals related to functions:</p>
<p><ul>
<li><p>Evaluate cube roots and absolute values</p></li>
<li><p>Graph eight basic functions</p></li> 
<li><p>Use horizontal and vertical asymptotes for graphing </p></li>
</ul></p>

<commentary audience="instructor"><title>Questions for Writing or Discussion</title>
<p><ol>
<li><p>Describe the differences between the graphs of <m>f(x)=x^2</m> and <m>g(x)=x^3</m>.</p></li>
